for a specic protein. The genes you inherit control what characteristics
you develop. Different genes control different characteristics and most
characteristics are controlled by multiple genes interacting. However, some
characteristics are controlled by a single gene — for example, red-green
colour blindness in humans and round vs wrinkly peas (see next page).
